I"R<h5 id="changing-beliefs">CHANGING BELIEFS</h5>

<p><img src="/materials/mettree.jpeg" width="500" /></p>

<div class="maintext">

  <div class="title"> INSTRUCTORS </div>

  <p>Nilanjan Das and Daniel Rothschild</p>

  <div class="title"> ABOUT </div>

  <p>Our knowledge and beliefs are always in flux. We will focus on the question of what norms, if any, govern changes in belief and knowledge over time. Each week will focus on a specific topic from the recent literature. Readings will include work by David Christensen, Maria Lasonen-Aarnio, Gilbert Harman, and Jane Friedman.</p>

  <div class="title"> MECHANICS </div>

  <p>The seminar meets Thursdays from 10am to 1pm in the seminar room of the UCL Philosophy Department, 19 Gordon Square.  There is no meeting on 2 June (a bank holiday). One extra session will be scheduled later.</p>

  <p>The module will be assessed by a 4500-word essay.</p>

  <p>Auditors and provocateurs welcome.</p>

